        {
          "language": "de",
          "role": "canonical_source",
          "text": "Segne den Becher, welcher überfliessen will, dass das Wasser golden aus ihm fliesse und überallhin den Abglanz deiner Wonne trage!"
        },
        {
          "language": "ru",
          "role": "working_translation",
          "text": "Благослови чашу,\nкоторая хочет перелиться,\nчтобы золото из неё текло\nи повсюду несло отблеск твоего ликования!"
        },
        {
          "language": "en",
          "role": "bridge_translation",
          "text": "Bless the cup that wants to overflow, so that the water may flow golden from it and carry everywhere the reflection of your bliss!"
        }
      ],
      "translation_tension": {
        "segment_id": "seg.1.1.1.10",
        "note": "'Abglanz' remains afterglow, reflection, or reflected radiance; witness layers should keep the difference between source light and carried shine. 'Wonne' and 'ликование' keep the image affectively high without collapsing into mere pleasure."
